# Struxa CMS version — bump and push on ship

When you **commit shippable CMS work** on this repo, bump all four Struxa release markers in the **same commit**:

1. **`src/CmsVersion.php`** → `CURRENT`
2. **`composer.json`** → `"version"`
3. **`README.md`** → `**Version:** …`
4. **`storage/cms-updates.example.json`** → `cms.latest_version`, `title`, `summary`

Use **patch** semver for fixes and small features (`1.1.59` → `1.1.60`). Use **minor** only when the user asks or the change is clearly breaking/new major surface.

Update **`summary`** in `cms-updates.example.json` to describe what that release actually ships.

**Plugin-only ZIP/catalog work** (under `plugins/` or `struxa-dist/zips/` for a single plugin): bump that plugin’s **`plugin.json`** → `"version"` as well. Still bump Struxa’s four files when core/templates/routes/docs in this repo changed in the same commit.

After a successful commit, **push to `origin`** on the current branch (see `git-push-after-commit.mdc`). Do not leave shipped work local-only unless the user explicitly asks to keep it local.

If merging an **upstream Struxa release** with a specific version number, set all four files to **that** release’s version in the merge commit.

The user may refer to this as “page number”; they mean **Struxa’s version number**, incremented when we ship from this repo.
